President Muhammadu Buhari, on Monday, inaugurated several projects in Kano state. The projects inaugurated by the president included the federal government’s tier IV data centre, described as “the first in northern Nigeria and the highest data centre in the world”, housing estate at Darmanawa royal city, Dala inland dry port, and Aliko Dangote ultra-modern skill acquisition centre. Buhari was received by Abdullahi Ganduje, Kano governor, while Isa Pantami, minister of communications and digital economy, was also in attendance. Below are pictures from the event.              